commit.message:
gm_s86dl.h: Use __kernel_daddr_t for solaris_x86_slice.s_start

musl libc does not define daddr_t as it's deprecated, therefore
use __kernel_daddr_t from <linux/types.h>.

Signed-off-by: Petr Vorel <petr.vorel@gmail.com>
Describe disabling a FS recognition module and add an example

Merge pull request #11 from harababurel/master

fixed README table
fixed README table
Use new travis build system

Respect configure --docdir option

Closes #10

Real fix for crash

Now we can work on a block device properly, closes #9 properly.

Fix crash on a non-disk device

Closes #9

gpart: avoid superfluous seek calls

The l64opush() logic would cause 2 lseek() syscalls per guess loop.
By simply seeking back after every probing call, we do with a single
seek() call.

gpart: use posix_fadvise to increase reading speed

Use fadvise to tell the OS to try readahead.

Speed up by reading larger chunks

Based on work initiated by mwilck
Format code with clang-format (mostly)
Add LVM2 and btrfs to list of supported modules

Merge pull request #8 from mwilck/export

Add LVM2 and Btrfs support

gpart: add btrfs support

Add support for detecting Btrfs volumes.

gpart: add support for LVM2 physical volumes

Add support for LVM2 PVs. It is very hard to do good consistency
checking for this format; that would require parsing the LVM2
text format. Thus only partition size is currently checked.

Merge pull request #7 from ian-abbott/readme-improvements

Readme improvements
README.md: Mention that the real chs range is tagged with 'r'.

README.md: Mention that the tool is for MBR-partitioned disks

since GPT partitions are not supported yet.

README.md: Remove phrase about dynamically loading modules.

Dynamic module loading is no longer supported.
README.md: A few spelling/consistency changes

README.md: add markdown to the output explanation

Format the output as code blocks and the commentary as block quotes.

README.md: Remove a lot of unnecessary indentation from paragraphs

The indentation in the paragraphs doesn't really help readability and
has no effect on the HTML output, so remove it.

README.md: markdown filenames

Use *emphasis* markers for filenames.

README.md: miscellaneous markdown changes in function descriptions

In the descriptions for the guessing module functions, use code markers
for inline code, and backslash escapes for special characters such as '*'
and '_'.

README.md: use block quotes for guessing module function descriptions

Improves the appearance of the HTML output
